  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Avoid it,.... As dangerous and pernicious, as abominable and detestable; or, \"flee from it\", as the Vulgate Latin version: Jarchi and Gersom interpret it, \"make it void\"; cause it to cease, destroy it, do all you can to hinder the wicked from accomplishing their designs; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "pass not by it; do not come near it; keep at a distance from it, that you may not be drawn into it; abstain from all appearance of evil, and everything that may lead to it; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "turn from it, and pass away; the Targum adds, \"from them\", from wicked men. This heap of words is used to show the danger of bad company; to dissuade from the least approach to it; and to express the vehement desire of the wise man to preserve his son, and all well inclined persons, from it. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "turn from it, and pass away; the Targum adds, \"from them\", from wicked men. This heap of words is used to show the danger of bad company; to dissuade from the least approach to it; and to express the vehement desire of the wise man to preserve his son, and all well inclined persons, from it. ",
            "children": []
